Description: Pottery jar, imitation of the Phoenician Bichrome ware; spherical body, neck and single handle missing; gritty brown clay; fugitive pink slip, decorated with black and red paint: vertical concentric circles on the sides.
Curator's comments: See Brissaud and Zivie-Coche - Tanis 1987-1997, (1998) p.117, 139, [pl.7b]. Compare P. M. Bikai, The Phoenician Pottery of Cyprus (Nicosia 1987), pl. XXIV, nos, 27, 29; pl. XXV, nos. 50-52. Bikai associates these jars with the "Kouklia Horizon", which she dates to circa 1050-850? BC (Bikai op. cit. p. 69).
